<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-07-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-07-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="280" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d280">
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Circular.]</seg></opener>
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Adams</persName></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi></placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-07-08"><hi rend="italic">July</hi> 8, 1865</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> The military commission appointed to try
                            the conspirators against the lives of the late and of the present
                            President, of members of the cabinet and others, has brought its
                            proceedings to a close by sentencing Mary E. Surratt <pb facs="0455" n="415" xml:id="pg_415"/> Lewis Payne, David E. Herold, and George
                            Atzerodt, to death by hanging; Samuel A, Mudd, Michael O’Laughlin, and
                            Samuel Arnold to imprisonment at hard labor for life, and Edward
                            Spangler to imprisonment for the term of six years at hard labor.</p>
                        <p>The sentence against the four first-named persons was yesterday carried
                            into effect.</p>
                        <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Charles Francis Adams,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi></p>
                            <p>[Same, <hi rend="italic">mutatis mutandis,</hi> to our principal
                                ministers abroad. ]</p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>